e%20saw%20vital%20pillars%20of%20communities%20in%20their%20hospitals%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20found%2C%20%26quot%3BSteward%2C%20Cerberus%2C%20and%20MPT%20saw%20only%20dollar%20signs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20as%20Steward%20sells%20off%20its%20remaining%2031%20hospitals%2C%20underserved%20communities%20are%20hoping%20the%20new%20owners%20will%20focus%20less%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-giving-up-medical-care-cant-afford-costs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextracting%20profits%20from%20the%20facilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20more%20on%20elevating%20the%20quality%20of%20care.%20But%20even%20under%20new%20ownership%2C%20it%20doesn't%20look%20as%20though%20much%20will%20change.%20For%20starters%2C%20MPT%20will%20still%20be%20collecting%20rent%20on%20at%20least%2015%20of%20the%20hospitals%2C%20most%20of%20which%20are%20already%20losing%20money.%20And%2012%20of%20the%20facilities%20have%20ended%20up%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20operators%20with%20track%20records%20of%20running%20hospitals%20into%20the%20ground%20%E2%80%94%20often%20through%20deals%20with%20none%20other%20than%20MPT.%20All%20of%20which%20means%20that%2C%20barring%20a%20financial%20miracle%2C%20it's%20likely%20the%20hospitals%20will%20soon%20be%20bankrupt%20again.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20think%20these%20hospitals%20can%20maintain%20any%20reasonable%20level%20of%20operation%20for%20more%20than%20nine%20to%2012%20months%20without%20permanent%20financial%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Justin%20Simon%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20hedge%20fund%20Jaspar%20Capital%2C%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20industry%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20disturbing%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20Steward's%20facilities%20reveals%20a%20deeper%20flaw%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-hospitals-corporations-charge-upfront-surgery-healthcare-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20healthcare%20infrastructure%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-hospital-wait-times-are-bad-physician-shortage-low-pay-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edistressed%20hospitals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20are%20now%20locked%20in%20a%20self-perpetuating%20cycle%20of%20looting%3A%20Facilities%20that%20have%20already%20been%20plundered%20can%20only%20be%20sold%20to%20others%20who%20will%20continue%20the%20plundering.%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20people%20who%20will%20buy%20them%20are%20people%20who%20are%20using%20them%20as%20an%20asset%20to%20be%20bought%20and%20sold%20and%20stripped%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Rosemary%20Batt%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20the%20Industrial%20and%20Labor%20Relations%20School%20at%20Cornell%20University.%20Steward's%20hospitals%20are%20in%20such%20dire%20financial%20straits%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20that%20MPT%20is%20supplying%20the%20new%20owners%20with%20nearly%20%24100%20million%20in%20loans%2C%20along%20with%20temporary%20rent%20relief%2C%20to%20purchase%20the%20facilities%20that%20MPT%20itself%20helped%20decimate%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20MPT%20will%20continue%20to%20collect%20rent%20on.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falmost-20-of-hospitals-in-the-us-are-in-bad-shape-according-to-morgan-stanley-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20dying%20hospitals%3C%2Fa%3E%20struggle%20to%20survive%2C%20the%20treatment%20being%20prescribed%20is%20often%20more%20of%20what's%20killing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EEight%20of%20Steward's%20hospitals%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20a%20fourth%20of%20those%20it%20was%20still%20operating%20%E2%80%94%20have%20ended%20up%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20a%20company%20called%20American%20Healthcare%20Systems.%20AHS%20and%20a%20related%20company%2C%20Healthcare%20Systems%20of%20America%2C%20are%20run%20by%20Michael%20Sarian%2C%20whose%20career%20echoes%20the%20approach%20to%20hospital%20management%20employed%20by%20Steward%20%E2%80%94%20including%20deals%20with%20MPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20founding%20AHS%2C%20Sarian%20served%20for%20eight%20years%20as%20president%20of%20another%20hospital%20company%2C%20Prime%20Healthcare%20Services.%20Prime%20touts%20itself%20as%20being%20in%20the%20business%20of%20shoring%20up%20distressed%20community%20hospitals%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bsaving%20hospitals%2C%20saving%20jobs%2C%20saving%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20declared%20on%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.primehealthcare.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20Justice%20Department%20has%20accused%20the%20system%20of%20a%20different%20motivation%3A%20inflating%20its%20profit%20through%20fraud.%20In%202018%2C%20Prime%20and%20its%20CEO%20agreed%20to%20pay%20%2465%20million%20to%20settle%20allegations%20that%20it%20had%20knowingly%20submitted%20false%20claims%20to%20Medicare%2C%20including%20for%20care%20that%20patients%20didn't%20need.%20Like%20Steward%2C%20the%20company%20has%20a%20history%20of%20extracting%20money%20from%20its%20hospitals%3A%20In%202007%2C%20Prime's%20financial%20statements%20disclosed%20that%20a%20family%20trust%20run%20by%20its%20founder%20received%20a%20distribution%20of%20over%20%2435%20million%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20all%20of%20it%20from%20MPT.%20And%20as%20with%20Steward%2C%20critics%20say%20the%20profits%20have%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20patients.%20Last%20October%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnational-nurses-united-213-nurses-died-from-covid-19-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Nurses%20United%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20America's%20largest%20organization%20of%20registered%20nurses%2C%20blasted%20the%20company%20for%20closing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-is-suddenly-obsessed-with-optimizing-childbirth-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematernity%20wards%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country.%20%26quot%3BPrime's%20focus%20on%20boosting%20profits%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20group%20said%2C%20had%20resulted%20in%20%26quot%3Bdrastic%20cuts%26quot%3B%20to%20care%2C%20%26quot%3Bparticularly%20impacting%20some%20of%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225781%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Glenwood%20Regional%20Medical%20Center's%20fa%C3%A7ade.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d064d1b8b41a9673fa4960%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223854%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGlenwood%20Regional%20in%20Louisiana%20is%20one%20of%20eight%20Steward%20hospitals%20that%20were%20taken%20over%20by%20AHS%2C%20which%20has%20come%20under%20fire%20for%20siphoning%20money%20out%20of%20medical%20centers%20it%20operates.%3Cp%3EBoston%20Globe%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Prime%20defended%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20care%20and%20said%20it%20settled%20the%20Medicare%20charges%20%26quot%3Bwith%20no%20findings%20of%20fault%26quot%3B%20and%20completed%20a%20government-mandated%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20integrity%20agreement.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20said%20it%20had%20allocated%20more%20than%20%241.4%20billion%20to%20buy%20back%20its%20real%20estate%20from%20MPT%2C%20which%20it%20said%20would%20result%20in%20%26quot%3Beven%20greater%20stability%20and%20security%20for%20its%20community%20hospitals%20and%20the%20vulnerable%20populations%20they%20are%20honored%20to%20serve.%26quot%3B%20But%20Prime%20has%20also%20issued%20%241.5%20billion%20in%20new%20debt%2C%20meaning%20its%20hospitals%20are%20still%20taking%20on%20obligations%20that%20they'll%20have%20to%20repay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pattern%20of%20plundering%20continued%20at%20American%20Healthcare%20Systems%2C%20which%20Sarian%20created%20in%202021%20after%20purchasing%20a%20bankrupt%20hospital%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20Lawsuits%20from%20vendors%20began%20to%20pile%20up%20almost%20immediately%2C%20along%20with%20reports%20from%20employees%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnurses-gig-work-apps-jobs-hospitals-pay-uber-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshort%20staffing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Regulators%20slapped%20AHS%20hospitals%20with%20notices%20of%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20jeopardy%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20its%20services%20were%20so%20shoddy%20that%20they%20could%20result%20in%20serious%20harm%20to%20patients.%20Before%20long%2C%20the%20company%20closed%20one%20of%20its%20hospitals%20and%20shuttered%20one%20of%20its%20emergency%20rooms.%20When%20AHS%20sought%20a%20waiver%20on%20a%20state%20loan%20it%20had%20used%20to%20buy%20the%20hospital%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20regulators%20learned%20that%20the%20company%20had%20transferred%20some%20%2411%20million%20out%20of%20the%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAHS%20also%20siphoned%20money%20out%20of%20Vista%20Medical%20Center%20East%2C%20another%20hospital%20it%20operates.%20Vista%2C%20which%20serves%20a%20low-income%20community%20in%20Illinois%2C%20recently%20furloughed%208.6%25%20of%20its%20workforce%20because%20of%20financial%20difficulties.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20care%20at%20the%20facility%20has%20suffered%3A%20On%20January%2023%2C%20a%20patient%20with%20hypothermia%20died%20after%20being%20found%20on%20the%20hospital's%20roof%20wearing%20only%20a%20hospital%20gown.%20Meanwhile%2C%20according%20to%20bankruptcy%20filings%2C%20Vista%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20applied%20for%20government%20support%20%E2%80%94%20has%20extracted%20millions%20of%20dollars%20from%20the%20hospital.%20%26quot%3BMoney%20should%20not%20be%20given%20to%20private%20equity%20entities%20at%20the%20taxpayer's%20expense%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20local%20coroner%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DUIOEhQO4cOg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20patient's%20death%2C%20%26quot%3Bespecially%20to%20a%20company%20with%20such%20a%20poor%20track%20record.%26quot%3B%20Some%20of%20the%20money%20AHS%20took%20from%20Vista%20has%20gone%20to%20support%20another%20of%20its%20hospitals%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20which%20owes%20rent%20to%20MPT.%20(Neither%20MPT%20nor%20AHS%20responded%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20none%20of%20this%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lawsuits%20from%20vendors%2C%20the%20substandard%20care%2C%20the%20sketchy%20deals%20%E2%80%94%20has%20prevented%20AHS%20from%20being%20permitted%20to%20take%20over%20eight%20of%20Steward's%20hospitals.%20Even%20though%20the%20company's%20dubious%20track%20record%20was%20well-documented%2C%20the%20bankruptcy%20court%20and%20government%20regulators%20have%20allowed%20the%20sale%20to%20go%20forward.%20%26quot%3BAHS%20has%20a%20history%20of%20terrible%20hospital%20operations%2C%20including%20accusations%20of%20looting%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Simon%2C%20the%20hedge%20fund%20director.%20Given%20the%20players%20involved%2C%20he%20warns%2C%20the%20cycle%20of%20collapse%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20repeat%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20companies%20that%20bought%20parts%20of%20Steward%20also%20have%20ties%20to%20MPT.%20Two%20of%20Steward's%20hospitals%20in%20West%20Texas%20are%20being%20purchased%20by%20Quorum%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20which%20is%20owned%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fportfolio-operations-jobs-rising-stars-of-private-equity-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate%20equity%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20a%20big%20investor%20in%20MPT's%20securities.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20Quorum%20has%20actually%20been%20on%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20hospital%20merry-go-round%3A%20It%20sold%20distressed%20facilities%20to%20both%20AHS%20and%20Steward%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20a%20private%20equity%20firm%20that%20sold%20off%20the%20underlying%20property%20to%20MPT.%20Now%2C%20according%20to%20Moody's%2C%20Quorum's%20debt%20is%20in%20%26quot%3Blimited%20default%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20it%20has%20missed%20or%20delayed%20a%20payment.%20It's%20unclear%20how%20Quorum%20will%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20its%20debt%20while%20funding%20any%20operating%20losses%20and%20capital%20expenditures%20needed%20at%20the%20two%20hospitals%20it's%20buying%20from%20Steward%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20the%20rent%20on%20the%20facilities%20it%20will%20owe%20to%20MPT.%20%26quot%3BThis%20sale%20demonstrates%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20current%20legal%20and%20regulatory%20system%20in%20protecting%20US%20healthcare%20infrastructure%20and%20access%20to%20quality%20care%20for%20patients%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpestakeholder.org%2Fnews%2Ftwo-steward-hospitals-acquired-by-private-equity-owned-system%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Private%20Equity%20Stakeholder%20Project%2C%20a%20watchdog%20group%20that%20tracks%20investment%20deals%20in%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20Steward's%20hospitals%20in%20Ohio%20have%20been%20sold%20to%20Insight%20Health%2C%20another%20company%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprospect.org%2Fhealth%2F2024-12-09-ambulance-chasers-totaled-hospitals%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echeckered%20track%20record%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20civil%20racketeering%20lawsuit%2C%20the%20insurance%20giant%20Allstate%20accused%20a%20hospital%20owned%20by%20the%20company%20of%20billing%20for%20patients%20who%20weren't%20really%20injured%2C%20and%20for%20procedures%20that%20were%20never%20performed.%20Insight%20denied%20the%20claims%2C%20and%20a%20settlement%20is%20pending.%20Although%20Insight%20purports%20to%20run%20some%20hospitals%20as%20nonprofits%2C%20filings%20show%20it%20has%20extracted%20exorbitant%20management%20fees%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%2012%25%20of%20the%20revenue%20in%20one%20case.%20(In%20a%20statement%20to%20BI%2C%20Insight%20said%20the%20fees%20%26quot%3Binclude%20executive%20services%2C%20software%2C%20legal%2C%20revenue%20cycle%20management%2C%20nursing%2C%20and%20clinical%20personnel%20and%20were%20provided%20at%20fair%20market%20value.%26quot%3B)%20Initially%2C%20the%20company%20tried%20to%20take%20over%20Steward's%20hospitals%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20only%20to%20be%20rebuffed%20by%20state%20regulators.%20Now%2C%20according%20to%20a%20form%20filed%20as%20part%20of%20the%20purchase%20in%20Ohio%2C%20Insight%20has%20received%20a%20loan%20from%20MPT%20using%20assets%20of%20the%20two%20hospitals%20it's%20acquiring%20from%20Steward%20as%20collateral.%20That%20means%20MPT%20will%20not%20only%20continue%20to%20collect%20rent%20on%20the%20facilities%2C%20albeit%20reduced%20for%20a%20time%2C%20but%20it%20will%20be%20owed%20a%20slice%20of%20the%20business%20if%20the%20hospitals%20go%20bankrupt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20Insight%20deal%20underscores%20what%20has%20become%20a%20vicious%20cycle%3A%20A%20hospital%20sells%20its%20real%20estate%20to%20MPT%2C%20pockets%20the%20proceeds%2C%20slashes%20care%2C%20and%20spirals%20into%20financial%20distress.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20the%20property%20is%20so%20troubled%20that%20MPT%20has%20to%20pay%20a%20buyer%2C%20sometimes%20one%20with%20few%20scruples%2C%20to%20take%20over%20the%20hospital%20and%20continue%20paying%20rent%20%E2%80%94%20which%20will%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20drive%20the%20new%20buyer%20out%20of%20business%20as%20well.%20The%20only%20winners%20are%20the%20investors%20who%20figure%20out%20ways%20to%20extract%20money%20from%20dying%20hospitals%20%E2%80%94%20and%20MPT%2C%20which%20gets%20to%20continue%20collecting%20rent.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20dirty%20end%20game%20of%20private%20equity%20failures%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Simon%2C%20the%20hedge%20fund%20director.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20deal%20goes%20poorly%2C%20there's%20only%20one%20way%20to%20get%20your%20money%20out%2C%20which%20is%20selling%20the%20real%20estate.%20And%20once%20you%20separate%20the%20ownership%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20from%20the%20operating%20hospital%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20for%20the%20bankruptcy%20court%20to%20give%20the%20hospital%20back%20to%20the%20community.%20They%20can't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20underserved%20communities%20continue%20to%20lose%20access%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctors-chief-medical-officers-healthcare-google-uber-salesforce-executives-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evital%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Regulators%20like%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20might%20be%20looking%20into%20MPT's%20deals%20on%20behalf%20of%20investors.%20But%20for%20all%20the%20political%20fury%20sparked%20by%20Steward's%20bankruptcy%2C%20no%20one%20appears%20to%20be%20ensuring%20that%20the%20new%20owners%20will%20provide%20for%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20communities%20their%20hospitals%20are%20meant%20to%20serve.%20%26quot%3BPoliticians%20keep%20railing%20against%20Steward%20and%20asking%20how%20this%20was%20allowed%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Richard%20Mortell%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20investor%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20industry.%20%26quot%3BMeanwhile%2C%20they%20are%20turning%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20the%20scam%20repeating%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20additional%20oversight%2C%20patient%20advocates%20warn%2C%20the%20looting%20of%20America's%20hospitals%20will%20continue%20unabated.%20%26quot%3BIt%20speaks%20to%20the%20failures%20of%20our%20regulatory%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mary%20Bugbee%2C%20who%20oversees%20healthcare%20research%20at%20the%20Private%20Equity%20Stakeholder%20Project.%20%26quot%3BThe%20system%20is%20not%20designed%20to%20ensure%20the%20hospitals%20are%20going%20to%20have%20the%20most%20reputable%20buyers%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20buyers%20who%20will%20keep%20hospitals%20open.%20It's%20possible%20the%20SEC%20is%20stepping%20in%20to%20protect%20investors%20and%20uphold%20the%20rules%20for%20public%20markets.%20But%20who%20is%20going%20to%20hold%20these%20entities%20accountable%20to%20patients%3F%20I%20don't%20see%20that%20happening%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fbethany-mc-lean%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EBethany%20McLean%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20special%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-hospitals-bankrupt-closing-wealthy-investors-looting-reselling-private-equity-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742206794000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b7613ceb4be2fff9a51fea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-hospitals-bankrupt-closing-wealthy-investors-looting-reselling-private-equity-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inside%20the%20financial%20scheme%20that's%20leaving%20America's%20hospitals%20on%20life%20support.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Bethany%20McLean)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-hospitals-bankrupt-closing-wealthy-investors-looting-reselling-private-equity-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ola%20Electric%20shares%20drop%207.2%25%20to%20record%20low%20after%20insolvency%20petition%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742206685000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fola-electric-shares-drop-7-2-to-record-low-after-insolvency-petition-125031700607_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rosmerta%20Digital%20Services%2C%20a%20vehicle%20registration%20service%20provider%20and%20a%20creditor%20of%20Ola%20Electric%20Technologies%2C%20filed%20a%20petition%20against%20the%20unit%20alleging%20default%20in%20payments%22%2C%22a