ers%20and%20managers%20are%20under%20tremendous%20pressure%20and%20usually%20review%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%20Your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20has%20to%20be%20optimized%20to%20catch%20their%20eye%20quickly.%20The%20goal%20is%20for%20them%20to%20skim%20it%20and%20think%20it%20would%20be%20worthwhile%20to%20interview%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20three%20biggest%20mistakes%20that%20could%20cost%20you%20the%20job%20you%20apply%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e4132df-a6f0-484f-a758-fec6d747283e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20No%20results%2C%20only%20activities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20most%20common%20mistake%20I%20see%20on%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s.%20People%20write%20down%20what%20they%20did%20by%20saying%20%26quot%3Bwrote%20code%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bmanaged%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bworked%20on%20X%20project.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenior%20performers%2C%20however%2C%20know%20they're%20valued%20for%20their%20impact%20and%20make%20a%20point%20to%20show%20the%20results%20of%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20rewrite%20nearly%20every%20bullet%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20in%20a%20way%20that%20describes%20why%20your%20work%20matters%20and%20shows%20that%20your%20presence%20made%20a%20positive%20difference%20to%20the%20team%2C%20the%20product%2C%20and%20the%20bottom%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20tricks%20to%20help%20do%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20possible%2C%20link%20to%20your%20results.%20People%20exaggerate%20and%20lie%20on%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20but%20nothing%20says%20%26quot%3Bmy%20work%20is%20real%26quot%3B%20like%20a%20link%20to%20the%20project.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20human%20eye%20is%20automatically%20drawn%20to%20bold.%20Selectively%20bold%20a%20few%20words%20or%20phrases%20to%20ensure%20your%20strongest%20accomplishments%20are%20noticed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUse%20action%20verbs%20like%20'owned%2C'%20'built%2C'%20'drove%2C'%20or%20'delivered.'%20This%20suggests%20you%20actively%20did%20something%20rather%20than%20simply%20witness%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeople%20believe%20specific%20numbers%2C%20including%20dollar%20figures.%20Use%20them%20when%20possible.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223edfad9d-ef37-47f6-b56d-ba96a6c4aacb%5C%22%3E2.%20No%20objective%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20an%20objective%2C%20a%20recruiter%20or%20hiring%20manager%20has%20to%20guess%20if%20you%20want%20the%20job.%20If%20you're%20a%20recruiter%20with%20a%20pile%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20waste%20your%20time%20doing%20any%20guessing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20objective%20clearly%20states%20what%20kind%20of%20role%20you're%20looking%20for%20in%20your%20next%20job%2C%20and%20a%20great%20objective%20is%20formulaic%20and%20short%20enough%20to%20be%20read%20in%20a%20single%20glance.%20Don't%20just%20talk%20about%20yourself%20in%20subjective%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20example%20of%20the%20formula%20for%20a%20senior%20engineer%20role%20would%20be%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3ESeeking%20a%20role%20as%20a%20Sr.%20Engineer%20where%20I%20can%20apply%20my%20proven%20ability%20shipping%20scaled%20services%20to%20deliver%20valuable%20innovation%20for%20the%20business.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20part%20simply%20states%20the%20role%20you%20seek.%20This%20is%20particularly%20important%20if%20you%20want%20to%20do%20something%20different%20from%20your%20last%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20part%20allows%20you%20to%20state%20your%20highest%20qualifications%20for%20a%20role.%20Highlight%20the%20top%20reason%20to%20put%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bcall%26quot%3B%20pile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20part%20shows%20you're%20there%20to%20help%20the%20manager%20and%20the%20company.%20While%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20job%26quot%3B%20for%20yourself%2C%20the%20manager%20is%20not%20focused%20on%20%26quot%3Bgiving%20someone%20a%20good%20job.%26quot%3B%20You%20want%20to%20convey%20that%20you're%20not%20just%20interested%20in%20yourself%20but%20that%20you're%20also%20dedicated%20to%20providing%20value%20to%20your%20new%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20my%20own%20objective%20in%20my%20executive%20coaching%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20as%20an%20example%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EObjective%3A%20Provide%20professional%20development%20at%20scale%2C%20guiding%20transitions%20to%20executive%20leadership.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EProven%20executive%20leadership%20of%20multiple%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%24500M%2B%20businesses%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20across%20games%2C%20video%2C%20apps%2C%20and%20music.%20Global%20leadership%20experience%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eteams%20800%2B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Technical%20inventor%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E60%2B%20issued%20patents%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252469195-2820-4e90-9124-fb948d3985d6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Too%20many%20words%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20are%20long%2C%20lasting%20three%20or%20more%20pages%20or%20using%20a%20tiny%20font%20to%20cram%20the%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mistake%20is%20writing%20what%20we%20want%20to%20write%20about%20rather%20than%20what%20the%20reader%20needs%20to%20know.%20I%20call%20these%20%26quot%3Bhappy%20words.%26quot%3B%20They%20occur%20when%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20opens%20with%20the%20candidate%20writing%20positive%20sentences%20about%20who%20they%20think%20they%20are.%20It%20looks%20like%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BMotivated%20self-starter%20looking%20for%20a%20positive%20environment%20where%20I%20can%20bring%20my%20technical%20skills%20and%20passion%20to%20a%20worthy%20project.%20Great%20coworker%20and%20mentor.%20Adaptable%2C%20fast%20learner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20natural%20to%20want%20to%20share%20what%20we%20see%20as%20our%20most%20positive%20traits.%20Unfortunately%2C%20managers%20looking%20at%20dozens%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20daily%20will%20ignore%20this%20because%20it%20doesn't%20tell%20what%20the%20candidate%20can%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20to%20follow%20is%20%26quot%3Bshow%2C%20don't%20tell.%26quot%3B%20If%20you're%20a%20fast%20learner%2C%20include%20bullets%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20that%20show%20this.%20For%20example%3A%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BLearned%20and%20applied%20X%20to%20project%20Y%2C%20going%20from%20first%20effort%20to%20customer%20shipment%20in%20nine%20weeks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20of%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20is%20to%20put%20your%20three%20best%20accomplishments%20per%20role%20in%20front%20of%20the%20manager.%20If%20you%20write%20too%20much%2C%20they%20will%20skim%20over%20your%20biggest%20accomplishments.%20It%20is%20best%20to%20keep%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20under%201%2C000%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20is%20700%20words%20long%20and%20covers%20a%2030-year%20career%2C%20and%20I%20created%20it%20on%20Microsoft%20Word%20in%20two%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you've%20written%20a%20solid%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20look%20out%20for%20these%20three%20more%20mistakes%20before%20applying%20to%20any%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c82811e-b92a-4538-ae17-8b70e0ebc391%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Optimizing%20for%20the%20Applicant%20Tracking%20System%20(ATS)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20try%20to%20cram%20keywords%20at%20the%20top%20to%20pass%20through%20the%20applicant%20tracking%20system.%20There%20are%20two%20significant%20problems%20with%20this%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%2080%25%20of%20all%20jobs%20go%20to%20someone%20with%20a%20networking%20connection%20to%20the%20role.%20Focusing%20on%20getting%20through%20the%20ATS%20means%20you're%20focusing%20on%20jobs%20where%20you%20have%20no%20networking%20connection%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20you're%20competing%20against%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20problem%20is%20that%20this%20makes%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20hard%20for%20a%20human%20to%20read%2C%20and%20it%20buries%20your%20strongest%20accomplishments%20in%20the%20body%20of%20the%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ideal%20approach%20is%20to%20write%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20for%20human%20eyes%2C%20then%20leverage%20your%20network%20to%20get%20it%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20someone%20who%20will%20read%20it.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20include%20keywords%2C%20put%20them%20at%20the%20end%20of%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20in%20a%20'skills'%20section.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22579b931f-e816-44f2-8954-ae81de96895c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Listing%20education%20and%20certifications%20in%20the%20wrong%20place%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20new%20graduate%2C%20the%20expected%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20format%20is%20to%20list%20your%20education%20at%20the%20top.%20If%20you%20have%20work%20experience%2C%20your%20education%20should%20be%20below%20your%20work%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20element%20of%20your%20education%20section%20is%20your%20GPA.%20If%20you%20do%20not%20list%20your%20GPA%2C%20the%20reader%20will%20assume%20it%20is%20poor.%20You're%20better%20off%20listing%20it%20if%20you%20did%20well%20(above%20a%203.3).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20can%20safely%20remove%20your%20GPA%20once%20you're%2010%20years%20out%20of%20school%2C%20if%20you%20graduated%20with%20honors%2C%20it%20may%20be%20worth%20keeping%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bottom%20of%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20is%20the%20place%20to%20list%20most%20certifications%20unless%20you%20have%20a%20critical%20attribute%20like%20security%20clearance%20or%20an%20expected%20certification%20for%20the%20role%20you%20seek.%20You%20can%20put%20those%20near%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c5ab821-29e9-47de-9bde-c46ea3efc5c8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Excluding%20hobbies%20and%20interests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20benefits%20to%20ending%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20with%20a%20little%20information%20about%20hobbies%2C%20charitable%20activities%2C%20and%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20interests%20humanize%20you.%20If%20someone%20has%20read%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20you%20won%20their%20attention.%20Giving%20a%20little%20personal%20texture%20at%20the%20bottom%20helps%20you%20be%20memorable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20managers%20and%20recruiters%20look%20for%20icebreakers%20if%20they%20call%20you.%20Maybe%20they%20ski%20or%20have%20a%20dog%2C%20too%2C%20so%20listing%20things%20like%20this%20creates%20more%20chances%20to%20connect%20emotionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2f56c8c-e52e-4429-a61f-8717f31604e0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENext%20steps%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you're%20confident%20in%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20don't%20procrastinate%20by%20continuing%20to%20polish%20it.%20Focus%20on%20networking%20to%20get%20a%20good%20reference%20for%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20last%20mistake%20I%20see%20is%20candidates%20failing%20to%20leverage%20their%20carefully%20crafted%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20language%20on%20LinkedIn.%20To%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20LinkedIn%2C%20put%20your%20crisp%20objective%20statement%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BAbout%26quot%3B%20section%20of%20the%20profile.%20Then%2C%20copy%20your%20job%20bullets%20into%20each%20section%20of%20%26quot%3BWork%20History.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFill%20out%20your%20education%20and%20other%20information%2C%20and%20keep%20it%20current.%20This%20way%2C%20recruiters%20can%20find%20you%20while%20you%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEthan%20Evans%20is%20a%20retired%20Amazon%20vice%20president%20with%20over%2023%20years%20of%20experience%20as%20a%20business%20executive.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-amazon-vp-shares-top-resume-mistakes-how-to-correct-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C