ew%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672dec57192f52589856e215%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFauxels%2FPexels%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGen%20Z%20workers%20aren't%20paying%20attention%20to%20traditional%20job%20advice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey're%20more%20willing%20to%20pursue%20their%20career%20goals%20through%20job-hopping%2C%20says%20a%20career%20coach.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20two%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20navigated%20the%20job-hopping%20process.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20secret%20that%20Gen%20Z%20has%20some%20untraditional%20views%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-job-satisfaction-unhappy-work-salary-promotion-loyalty-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20not%20afraid%20of%20breaking%20workplace%20taboos%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-happy-job-hopping-quit-without-backup-oliver-wyman-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob-hopping%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they're%20willing%20to%20prioritize%20their%20well-being%20and%20happiness%20over%20higher%20pay.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20are%20taking%20this%20mindset%20to%20the%20next%20step%20by%20quitting%20their%20jobs%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20months%20%E2%80%94%20breaking%20the%20classic%20recommendation%20of%20staying%20at%20a%20job%20for%20a%20year%20or%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDennis%20Xiao%20is%20one%20of%20those%20people.%20After%20graduating%20college%20in%202021%2C%20Xiao%20started%20working%20at%20an%20investment%20bank%20but%20soon%20realized%20he%20didn't%20feel%20fulfilled%20by%20the%20job.%20Six%20months%20in%2C%20Xiao%20decided%20to%20quit.%20Since%20then%2C%20Xiao%20has%20worked%20a%20strategic%20finance%20role%20at%20WeWork%2C%20taken%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffire-millennials-mini-retiring-early-financial-independence-career-break-burnout-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecareer%20break%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20travel%2C%20and%20been%20self-employed%20as%20a%20content%20creator%20and%20coach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoey%20H.%2C%20who%20declined%20to%20provide%20his%20last%20name%20for%20privacy%20reasons%2C%20had%20a%20similar%20experience.%20He%20got%20a%20job%20as%20a%20software%20developer%20at%20a%20small%20startup%20in%20October%202021%20but%20left%20after%20eight%20months%20because%20he%20didn't%20feel%20like%20the%20company%20offered%20strong%20career%20development%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20find%20an%20environment%20where%20I%20could%20have%20more%20support%2C%20maybe%20at%20a%20larger%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Joey%20said.%20He's%20since%20found%20another%20software%20developer%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECareer%20coach%20Marnie%20Lemonik%20has%20seen%20this%20new%20attitude%20toward%20work%20play%20out%20among%20her%20clients.%20%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20trend%20that%20I've%20noticed%20with%20Gen%20Z%20is%20they%20have%20more%20inherent%20confidence%20in%20themselves%20in%20the%20work%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Lemonik%20said.%20%26quot%3BMillennials%20tend%20to%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20guilt-ridden%20about%20that%20process%2C%20and%20they're%20more%20concerned%20with%20leaving%20a%20job%20after%20only%20a%20year%20and%20the%20optics%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob-hopping%20isn't%20an%20easy%20task%2C%20especially%20early%20on%20in%20your%20career.%20Here's%20what%20can%20make%20the%20transition%20smoother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263a8c2a2-4612-4c27-947d-5e7e0756c89c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrepare%20early%20and%20build%20an%20emergency%20fund%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Gen%20Zers%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20confident%20in%20their%20abilities%20to%20land%20a%20new%20job%2C%20the%20process%20isn't%20always%20seamless%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20you're%20leaving%20without%20another%20job%20lined%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20this%20desire%20to%20think%2C%20'Once%20I%20start%20job%20searching%2C%20I'll%20find%20a%20job%20in%20a%20month%2C'%20or%2C%20'I%20have%20a%20really%20good%20network%2C%20so%20maybe%20I'll%20find%20a%20job%20within%20two%20months.'%20The%20very%20rough%20average%20I've%20seen%20across%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20levels%20of%20my%20clients%20is%20three%20to%20six%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20Lemonik%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20longer%20period%20of%20time%20than%20what%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20budget%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20that%20reason%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20have%20an%20adequate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20act%20as%20a%20buffer%20between%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20two%20months%20for%20Joey%20to%20find%20another%20job%20after%20quitting%20his%20first%20one%2C%20but%20he%20had%20begun%20preparing%20for%20interviews%20many%20months%20before%20leaving.%20Planning%20a%20few%20months%20ahead%2C%20getting%20a%20head%20start%20on%20interviewing%2C%20and%20putting%20more%20money%20into%20savings%20leading%20up%20to%20your%20departure%20can%20make%20the%20job-hopping%20process%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2221f2a0c8-48dd-468f-86f5-ca13a8785624%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsider%20decreasing%20your%20401(k)%20contributions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20bad%20idea%20to%20decrease%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20you're%20contributing%20to%20your%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20you%20plan%20to%20leave%20your%20current%20job%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20Xiao%20did%20when%20he%20started%20planning%20to%20leave%20his%20second%20job.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'I'm%20just%20going%20to%20start%20redirecting%20money%20away%20from%20my%20401(k)%20to%20pure%20savings%20to%20prepare%20for%20this%20chapter%20of%20not%20having%20income%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20money%20is%20in%20your%20401(k)%2C%20it's%20locked%20up%20for%20the%20long%20term%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can't%20withdraw%20it%20before%20age%2059%20%C2%BD%20without%20a%2010%25%20penalty%20and%20income%20taxes.%20Lowering%20your%20contributions%20will%20give%20you%20more%20immediate%20cash%20flow.%20This%20can%20be%20especially%20advantageous%20if%20you're%20early%20on%20in%20your%20career%20and%20earning%20an%20entry-level%20salary.%20If%20that's%20the%20case%2C%20prioritize%20your%20immediate%20financial%20needs%20by%20diverting%20cash%20to%20a%20savings%20account%20instead%20of%20maxing%20out%20retirement%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDecreasing%20your%20401(k)%20contributions%20can%20sound%20risky%20if%20you're%20concerned%20about%20hitting%20your%20retirement%20goals%2C%20but%20many%20people%20job-hop%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrew-salary-from-40000-to-225000-job-hopping-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasing%20their%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20benefits.%20Joey's%20first%20employer%20didn't%20offer%20a%20401(k)%20match%2C%20so%20he%20gained%20a%20better%20benefits%20package%20by%20switching%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239b7ce86-8c54-460f-81d6-6b1213c1db06%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20a%20'bridge%20job'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bridge%20job%20is%20a%20position%20that%20serves%20as%20a%20stepping%20stone%20between%20your%20current%20job%20and%20your%20dream%20job.%20Beyond%20providing%20you%20with%20income%20while%20you%20search%20for%20a%20job%2C%20a%20bridge%20job%20can%20help%20build%20up%20the%20professional%20skills%20needed%20for%20you%20to%20get%20closer%20to%20the%20career%20you